<HEADLINE> French Judges End Inquiry into Roland Dumas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dumas, 76, who served as foreign minister under President
Francois Mitterrand and is now president of France's top legal
authority, the Council of State, was accused of abusing social
properties and concealing his participation in the act by
conspiring with his former mistress Christine Deviers-Joncour and
others.
</P>
<P>
The judges did not reveal the outcome of the investigation by
the two judges, Eva Joly and Laurent Vichnievsky. Judicial
sources said they will most likely send Dumas and the others
involved in the case back to court for further investigation.
</P>
<P>
