payment and millions of francs in commissions from the oil group
Elf-Aquitaine from 1989 to 1993.
</P>
<P>
In one particular incident, Elf won support and approval from
Dumas, who was then serving as foreign minister, in a 1992 deal
involving the sale of three French frigates to Taiwan. 
