<HEADLINE> Premier Zhu Presides Over Executive Meeting of State Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji presided
over an executive meeting of the State Council this afternoon to
discuss and pass two draft laws on the execution of the detailed
regulations of the land administration and on the protection of
farmland.
</P>
<P>
Big changes have been made in the drafts with regard to the
detailed regulations for the Implementation of Land Administration
Law which was promulgated by the State Council on January 4th,
1991.
</P>
<P>
The draft laws have tougher stipulations on land registration,
overall planning of land utilization and the procedures for land
application for construction purposes, and detailed stipulations
on the planning and acreage of farmland protection zones.
</P>
<P>
The State Council is expected to promulgate the two laws after
further revisions. 
