<HEADLINE> Exhibition On Guangzhou's Opening Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on the 20
years of opening-up in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the exhibition showed that from 1978 to 1997, the
city had used a total of 13.94 billion U.S. dollars of overseas
funds, with an yearly rise of 37.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
From January to November this year, the city had used a total
of 2.67 billion U.S. dollars of overseas funds, 5.7 percent more
than in the same 1997 period, despite the financial turmoil in
southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's export volume of this year may reach 8 billion
U.S. dollars, up 6.5 percent than last year.
</P>
<P>
At present the number of overseas-funded enterprises in
Guangzhou has topped 8,400, contributing some 42 percent of the
city's total industrial output value, according to the
exhibition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
