People's Bank of China, the country's central bank, will build a
financial security zone across Shanghai and the two provinces of
Fujian and Zhejiang to promote the economic growth of the area,
said a local banker today.
</P>
<P>
To this end, the Shanghai branch of the central bank will try
to use more overseas funds with its good financial order and
service, Wu Xiaoling, director of the branch told a press
conference for Shanghai-based overseas reporters here today.
</P>
