<HEADLINE> Indian Rewards to Its Winners at Asiad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Atal Behari
Vajpayee on Thursday announced cash rewards to Indian Asian Games
athletes who won medals in Bangkok, reports said.
</P>
<P>
According to Vajpayee, each gold medal winner would get
500,000 rupees (12,500 U.S. dollars), while silver and broze
medallists would receive 300,000 rupees (7,500 U.S. dollars) and
200,000 rupees (5,000 U.S. dollars) respectively.
</P>
<P>
The awards were higher than those previously given by Indian
governments to winners at international meets.
</P>
<P>
India won seven golds, 11 silver and 17 bronze medals at the
Bangkok Games. 
</P>
