<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Five officials from three
opposition parties in Zambia have resigned to join the
newly-formed United Party for National Development (UPND) led by
presidential aspirant Anderson Mazoka, Times of Zambia reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Lima Party (LP) chairman for information and publicity
Stanford Hlazo, Lusaka province chairman Stanley Ngwenya and
secretary Lewis Kayokolo have joined the UPND formed last month,
said the daily newspaper.
</P>
<P>
