<DOCNO> XIE19981224.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Million Cranes Visit China Each Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Between two and three million
cranes migrate to China each year for breeding and to spend the
winter, thanks to improved environmental conditions.
</P>
<P>
Most of those cranes spend their winter in northeastern China,
or along the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River or on
the Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau in southwestern China, according to
specialists attending an international forum on environment.
</P>
<P>
China has established 50 nature reserves primarily for cranes
and has research programs to study their migration routes and
habitats.
</P>
<P>
China is home to nine of world's 15 crane species. 
</P>
</TEXT>
