<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Outstanding Shanghai Housing Loans Hit 15.2 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Outstanding housing loans to
Shanghai residents stand at 15.2 billion yuan, according to a
recent reports released by the Shanghai Branch of the People's
Bank of China (PBOC), the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding volume includes loans of 8.19 billion yuan from
the aggregate public fund and 7.01 billion yuan in commercial
loans.
</P>
<P>
From January to November, commercial banks extended housing
loans totalling 9.22 billion yuan, with outstanding loans
accounting for 7.69 billion yuan of the total.
</P>
<P>
Projections indicate that some one million people have received
loans during 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
