level of 490 million tons, according to Minister of Agriculture
Chen Yaobang.
</P>
<P>
Chen said the cotton output was lower than last year, but noted
that the total output of more than 4.2 million tons will meet
demand on the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
--The former deputy director of Jinan Customs has been given a
life sentence by the Supreme People's Court for participating in a
smuggling racket.
</P>
<P>
Gao Qingting was also deprived of lifelong political rights and
also had part of his property confiscated.
</P>
<P>
A junior official in his department also received a three year
jail sentence for helping Gao.
</P>
<P>
--China expects to maintain grain output at 490 million tons,
this year's total, or above next year, said Minister of
Agriculture Chen Yaobang at a press conference here yesterday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Chen said cotton output will be about 3.5 million tons in 1999,
lower than the 4.2 million tons for this year, and the output of
meat, marine products, and other farm produce will be increased
steadily next year. 
</P>
