<HEADLINE> Biography of Famous Chinese Scholar Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The first biography of Ji
Xianlin, one of China's prominent academic figures, was recently
published in China by the Shanxi Classics Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
Its author is Professor Cai Degui of Shandong University.
</P>
<P>
Ji Xianlin was vice-president of Beijing University and a
well-known scholar in modern China. He is especially accomplished
in Oriental literature, Indian studies, and Buddhism.
</P>
<P>
The 640,000-character book gives a thorough account of Ji's
many experiences from son of a farmer family to prominent scholar
and shows the Chinese intellectual's virtues of patriotism,
devotion to work, and diligence.  
</P>
