<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese City Projects Open for Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The city of Chongqing
recently released a list of projects for 1999 that are open to
overseas investors, which need 15.6 billion yuan in investment.
</P>
<P>
A municipal government official said that the 26 major projects
are mainly in infrastructure, industrial development, science and
technology, agriculture, tourism, and real estate.
</P>
<P>
In the 1996-2000 period, Chongqing will focus on pillar
industries like machine building centering on automobile and
motorcycle production, the chemical industry based on the use of
natural gas and pharmaceuticals production, and the steel- and
aluminum-based metallurgy industry.
</P>
<P>
It will also promote the development of electronic information,
building materials, tourism, and food industries, and reinforce
agriculture industrialization, high-tech industries, and
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, Chongqing will become a regional center of
trade, finance, transportation, and telecommunications center for
the upper reaches of the Yangtze River.  
</P>
