England, an area badly hit by the manufacturing downturn and
strong pound.
</P>
<P>
Byers was elected to parliament for Wallsend in 1992, moving to
North Tyneside, a prosperous suburb of Newcastle, in the 1997
boundary change.
</P>
<P>
He took a law degree at Liverpool Polytechnic and was a law
lecturer at Newcastle Polytechnic before entering politics.
</P>
