evacuated to Jordan in the U.S.-British bombardment against Iraq
last week returned to Baghdad Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
But the number of the returned relief workers is not
immediately known.
</P>
<P>
U.N. sources here told Xinhua that more U.N. humanitarian
staff will come back in the coming few days.
</P>
