<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A senior Ugandan official has
denied responsibility in the award of the fraudulent contract
which caused the loss of over three billion Shillings (3 million
U.S. Dollars) meant for valley dams and valley tanks in
the southwestern region.
</P>
<P>
Kezimbira Miyingo, State Minister for Agriculture in charge of
Animal Industry, made the denial at parliament Wednesday, Radio
Uganda reported in the evening.
</P>
