<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Calls for Law to Protect Natural </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian
Environmental Protection Authority Wednesday called for a law to
protect natural resources from man-made and natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a national meeting on the draft environmental
protection law here, Tewolde-Brirhan Gebre-Egziabher, general
manager of the Authority, said that the national environmental
protection policy approved a year ago in Ethiopia has not been
translated into law due to capacity limitation.
</P>
